{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Store internals have been rewritten for performance and future features, and are now compatible with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SwiftUI’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"text":" property wrapper.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.15","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.14","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.13","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.12","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.11","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.10","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.8","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.7","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.6","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.5","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.4"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"type":"text","text":" that one should be aware of."}]},{"text":"Store internals rewrite","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"test your application after upgrading."}]},{"anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","text":"StateObject compatibility","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One important difference between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"text":" is that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"eager, while "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"text":"‘s is lazy. Because of this, if you initialize a root ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"type":"text","text":" to be held"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":", stores will be initialized (and immediately discarded) whenever the parent view’s body"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is computed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To avoid the creation of these stores, one can now assign the store to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":", instead:"}]},{"code":["struct FeatureView: View {","  @StateObject var store: StoreOf<Feature>","","  init() {","    _store = StateObject(","      \/\/ This expression is only evaluated the first time the parent view is computed.","      wrappedValue: Store(initialState: Feature.State()) {","        Feature()","      }","    )","  }","","  var body: some View { \/* ... *\/ }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The store’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"ObservableObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance does not have any impact on the actual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"observability of the store. You should continue to rely on the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/ObservableState()","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" macro for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"observation."}]}],"name":"Important","style":"important"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.19"]}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Migrating to 1.19","roleHeading":"Article","modules":